# Pricing Posture in Replies

> [!note] For this tenant
> Pricing strategy is: **{{kb.pricing_posture_label}}**

## Standing rule

Pricing is OK in REPLIES. It is only blocked in cold OUTBOUND copy.

## Default posture: {{kb.pricing_posture_label}}

{{#if kb.pricing_posture_is_share_upfront}}
When a prospect asks "how much?", share your standard pricing details upfront. This builds trust and filters for budget-qualified prospects.
{{/if}}

{{#if kb.pricing_posture_is_defer_to_call}}
When a prospect asks "how much?", defer to a discovery call. This keeps the conversation moving and lets you understand their needs first.

**Recommended reply:** "Happy to discuss pricing once I understand your situation better. Let's jump on a quick call — I can show you what's relevant and you'll have a clear sense of the investment."
{{/if}}

{{#if kb.pricing_posture_is_range_only}}
When a prospect asks "how much?", share only a price range without exact tier details. This indicates scale without boxing you in for custom deals.
{{/if}}

## What's OK to share post-reply

{{#if kb.post_reply_pricing}}
{{kb.post_reply_pricing}}
{{else}}
(Not specified — refer to your account manager if this comes up.)
{{/if}}

## What NEVER to share in a reply

- Enterprise custom pricing
- Competitor price comparisons
- Discount codes (unless prospect explicitly qualifies)
- Internal cost structure or margin details
- Payment plan options (defer to call)

## Escalation path

If the prospect disputes pricing or asks for a custom quote, escalate to your account manager via Telegram notification.
